### Rust: Implement Custom Formatting Helper Struct

Source: https://github.com/astral-sh/ruff/blob/main/crates/ruff_python_formatter/CONTRIBUTING.md

Demonstrates creating a helper struct `FormatEmptyParenthesized` in Rust to abstract formatting logic. It requires implementing the `Format<PyFormatContext<'_>>` trait and provides a constructor function `empty_parenthesized` for easier usage. This pattern is useful for reusable formatting components.

```rust
/// Helper to hide the fields for the struct
pub(crate) fn empty_parenthesized<'content>(
    comments: &'content [SourceComment],
    has_plus_prefix: bool,
) -> FormatEmptyParenthesized<'content> {
    FormatEmptyParenthesized {
        comments,
        has_plus_prefix,
    }
}

/// The wrapper struct
pub(crate) struct FormatEmptyParenthesized<'content> {
    comments: &'content [SourceComment],
    has_plus_prefix: bool,
}

impl Format<PyFormatContext<'_>> for FormatEmptyParenthesized<'_> {
    /// Here we implement the actual formatting
    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut Formatter<PyFormatContext>) -> FormatResult<()> {
        if self.has_plus_prefix {
            text("+ ").fmt(f)?; // This is equivalent to `write!(f, [text("*")])?;`
        }
        write!(
            f,
            [
                text("("),
                soft_block_indent(&dangling_comments(&self.comments)),
                text(")")
            ]
        )
    }
}

